title: Tech Stocks This Week
text: Here's a look at Fitbit and Facebook's latest announcements  -- and why Eventbrite stock plummeted.

title: Facebook blocks ads for women with menopause but allows ads selling pills for erectile dysfunction
text: Facebook is preventing a number of companies that sell lubricants for women going through menopause to advertise on its service despite allowing ads for equivalent products from brands that target men.

title: Facebook removes fake accounts that tried to stir hate and political division in the UK and Romania
text: Facebook says one page in the U.K. was followed by about 175,000 users, while an Instagram account had gained 4,500 followers.

title: This could change Facebook forever
text: Mark Zuckerberg’s new plan to pivot Facebook privacy means investing most of its energy into groups and messaging products like Messenger, Instagram, and WhatsApp.

title: Zuckerberg's privacy push could become 'an excuse for Facebook to dodge responsibility': UK lawmaker
text: British MP Damian Collins, an outspoken Facebook critic, said it would be understandable if people do not trust Zuckerberg's "sudden change of heart" in advocating for more privacy on the company's platforms.

title: Facebook takes on anti-vaccination misinformation
text: Dr. Janette Nesheiwat on Facebook's plans to combat vaccination misinformation on the social media platform and calls for more transparency related to health care costs.

title: Facebook Is Missing a Big Opportunity With Messaging, BTIG Analyst Says
text: BTIG analyst Rich Greenfield, Wired Magazine Editor-in-Chief Nick Thompson and Bloomberg's Sarah Frier discuss Facebook Inc.'s shift toward privacy and encryption. They speak with Bloomberg's Emily Chang on "Bloomberg Technology."

title: Facebook won't show content containing vaccine misinformation
text: CNBC's Julia Boorstin reports on Facebook's announcement that it will reject ads or content containing vaccine misinformation.

title: Zuckerberg has given us no reason to believe him
text: Mark Zuckerberg signalled a major shift at Facebook, but history shows he often fails to deliver on promises.

title: Why did Facebook lose an estimated 15 million users in the past two years?
text: The slump was most pronounced among kids and young adults, according to a new report.

title: Facebook has a 'privacy focused vision,' says Mark Zuckerberg
text: Dan Howley and Dan Roberts of Yahoo Finance discuss Facebook's new privacy policy.

title: Jim Cramer on Facebook
text: Jim Cramer & Katherine Ross on the floor of the NYSE.

title: Why this expert says Facebook needs to focus on Instagram
text: Business Insider's Henry Blodget and Foundation Capital General Partner Paul Holland join CNBC's "Squawk Alley' team to discuss Facebook's pivot to privacy after repeated scandals.

title: Facebook pivots to privacy after numerous scandals
text: CNBC's Julia Boorstin reports on Mark's Zuckerberg's announcement to pivot Facebook into a company focused on privacy. This comes as Facebook has been battling scandal after scandal related to data breaches and privacy issues.

title: Facebook's Zuckerberg Presents 'Privacy-Focused Vision'
text: Facebook, Inc. (FB) co-founder and CEO Mark Zuckerberg shared his "vision and principles" for a privacy-focused messaging and social networking platform in an open Facebook post Wednesday

title: Zuckerberg trying to reverse Facebook's negative public image with privacy push?
text: Walser Wealth Management President Rebecca Walser on Facebook's privacy push and the state of the markets.

title: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg's privacy pledge raising more questions than answers?
text: BigEyedWish founder Ian Wishingrad on Facebook's new focus on privacy may impact the social media giant's business model.

title: Facebook Privacy Battle Will Center on Messaging, Activate CEO Says
text: acebook Inc. Chief Executive Officer Mark Zuckerberg says the future of his company’s product development will be focused on encrypted, private and ephemeral communication.

title: Final Trade: Starbucks, Facebook, XOP & Zynga
text: The "Fast Money" traders share their final trades of the day including Starbucks, Facebook and more.

title: These three stocks are gearing up for a big breakout: Microsoft, Facebook & Bank of America
text: Chris Verrone, Strategas, on whether stocks are set up for new highs. With CNBC's Melissa Lee and the Fast Money traders, Tim Seymour, Brian Kelly, Chris Verrone and Steve Grasso.

title: Facebook to allow users to message across different apps
text: CNBC's Julia Boorstin reports on Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg's announcement the company will integrate messengers on social media.

title: Teen takes on Facebook over spread of vaccination myths
text: Dr. Mikhail Varshavski and Ethan Lindenberger, who got vaccinated against his mother's wishes, discuss concerns over the spread of misinformation on health-care issues such as vaccinations.

title: Here's why Wall Street is catching FANG fever again
